— 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FEEEFDD4FE72FDD8" box="[320,445,554,580]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFF818532FF13FDB0FF0BFCF9" blockId="38.[136,1452,554,869]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FF13FDB0FEE9FDF4" bold="true" box="[189,294,590,616]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Notes:—</emphasis>
This proliferous species was described from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FCB1FDB0FC55FDF4" box="[799,922,590,616]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
in 1923 by Ames and reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFF818532FA8AFDB1FA64FDF4" author="Luer, C. A." box="[1316,1451,590,617]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer (1992)</bibRefCitation>
to occur also in 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FEECFD8DFE54FD11" box="[322,411,627,653]" name="Panama" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FE7AFD8CFDFBFD10" box="[468,564,626,652]" name="Ecuador" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. However, as discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFF818532FCC0FD8CFAD8FD10" author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[878,1303,626,653]" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref31437" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2020) Revision of the Costa Rican species of Myoxanthus (Pleurothallidinae: Orchidaceae). Phytotaxa 448: 1 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 448.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, the material from 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FF67FD69FEEDFD2D" box="[201,290,663,689]" name="Panama" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FEF0FD68FE74FD2C" box="[350,443,662,688]" name="Ecuador" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
belongs to different species. The Ecuadorian plants are likely to be 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FB77FD69FABBFD2C" authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1241,1396,662,688]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FB77FD69FABBFD2C" box="[1241,1396,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FF26FD45FEDBFD48" box="[136,276,698,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="penellius">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FF26FD45FEDBFD48" box="[136,276,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. penellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
notes), whereas those cited for 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFF818532FDD1FD45FD17FD49" box="[639,728,699,725]" name="Panama" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Panama</collectingCountry>
are 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FCA5FD45FC60FD48" authorityName="Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" box="[779,943,699,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panamense">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FCA5FD45FC60FD48" box="[779,943,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. panamense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FC11FD44FB78FD48" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[959,1207,698,724]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scandens">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FC11FD44FB78FD48" box="[959,1207,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">Myoxanthus scandens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF818532FA23FD45FF34FD64" authorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Rojas-Alv. &amp; Karremans" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="38" pageNumber="249" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pennellius">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FA23FD45FF34FD64" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">M. pennellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former is recognized by its sepals with an acute apex 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FC16FD21FC00FD64" box="[952,975,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">vs</emphasis>
. obtuse to round, wider petals basally that conspicuously contract into a thickened narrow apex 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FD4CFCFDFCCEFC80" box="[738,769,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">vs.</emphasis>
narrowly ovate petals, slightly contracted above the middle, a lip with two longitudinal lamellae above the middle 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF818532FD47FCD9FCCFFCDC" box="[745,768,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="249">vs</emphasis>
. lip with two longitudinal lamellae from the base to near the apex.
</paragraph>
